    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <head>No. 439.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Manning</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-03-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 17,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your No. 84 has just reached this Department. The purport of my telegram of
                        March 7 last has not been understood.</p>
                <p>Whether the persons rescued are or are not Mexicans, nothing can satisfy the
                        Government of the United States except the delivery to its authorities of
                        the prisoners who were forcibly taken from the Arizona officials.</p>
                <p>The alternative offered in my telegram before mentioned only concerned the
                        Mexicans Who effected the rescue.</p>
            </div>
